This species honors Professor Philip J. Darlington, Jr., who among his many roles, systematically collected carabid beetles across Australia, and served as the first post-doctoral supervisor for Dr. Terry L. Erwin (
Kavanaugh 2020
). Terry championed a Darlingtonian world view regarding the diversification of carabid beetles (
Erwin 1981
), never losing sight of those questions that tied both men to primary observations made over long careers spent in the field.
